<section class="ct-u-marginBottom80">
    <div class="container">


        <div class="ct-infoBox ct-infoBox--type1">
            <div class="ct-infoBox-media ct-infoBox-media--left">
                <figure>
                    <img class="ct-infoBox-image--square" src="assets/images/farm/jessaTiller.jpg" alt="">
                </figure>
            </div>

            <div class="ct-infoBox-content">
                <div class="ct-infoBox-title">
                    <h3>community</h3>
                </div>

                <div class="ct-infoBox-text">
                    <p> Food is, at its most basic level, about two things: nutrition and community. We cannot think of any job we would rather do than build a loving, supportive, strong, energetic community of people who share the same or similar values as us. We want to help people in our physical community to become more knowledgeable about what they put into their bodies and the impact it has on both their health and the earth.  Community to us means connection - connection to one another through gatherings and conversation and connection to the land and the animals that we rely on.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ct-infoBox ct-infoBox--type1">
            <div class="ct-infoBox-media ct-infoBox-media--right">
                <figure>
                    <img class="ct-infoBox-image--square" src="assets/images/farm/chickenPlanter.jpg" alt="">
                </figure>
            </div>

            <div class="ct-infoBox-content">
                <div class="ct-divider ct-divider--big ct-u-marginBottom30"></div>

                <div class="ct-infoBox-title">
                    <h3>transparency</h3>
                </div>

                <div class="ct-infoBox-text">
                    <p>
						We believe that we can learn more from each other when information is
						freely available. We welcome the ideas and information of our peers and
						ancestors and will endeavor to contribute to the farming community in
						the same way. We want our Tribe to know exactly how we farm and why we
						farm that way so that they can make informed decisions about their
						options.
					</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ct-infoBox ct-infoBox--type1">
            <div class="ct-infoBox-media ct-infoBox-media--left">
                <figure>
                    <img class="ct-infoBox-image--square" src="assets/images/farm/jessaHorseshoe.jpg" alt="">
                </figure>
            </div>

            <div class="ct-infoBox-content">
                <div class="ct-divider ct-divider--big ct-u-marginBottom30"></div>

                <div class="ct-infoBox-title">
                    <h3>sustainability and regeneration</h3>
                </div>

                <div class="ct-infoBox-text">
                    <p>
						Because our health is directly tied to the health of the environment, we
						will strive to produce healthful foods in a way that improves our space
						and community, rather than depleting it. We will use financially and
						environmentally sustainable production methods and, wherever possible,
						regenerative methods.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

